comments: Wall (HOU) legally contests Doncic (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes marginal contact with Olynyk's (HOU) body after the rebound.
Olynyk (DAL) and Brunson (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Doncic (DAL) does not get ball height when he makes contact with Wall's (HOU) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (HOU) makes marginal contact to Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) arm after the release of affect his jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (HOU) moves alongside Doncic's (DAL) path when incidental contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Wall's (HOU) arm is already extended as he places a resting hand to Finney-Smith's (DAL) backside and he does not apply force during his jump shot attempt.
Wall (HOU) briefly places his hand on Doncic's (DAL) body and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (DAL) commits a take foul on Wall (HOU).
Tate (HOU) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Tate (HOU) moves along Doncic's (DAL) path when marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Tate (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position when incidental body contact occurs during Brunson's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) commits a take foul on Porter Jr. (HOU).
Wood (HOU) deflects Finney-Smith's (DAL) pass attempt in the lane before incidental contact occurs.
